SportsMed Physical Therapy is looking for Patient Transport Drivers. If you are a people person who enjoys helping others, are motivated and want to make a difference, this is a terrific opportunity to work in a job that offers variety and a great work environment.  

SportsMed Physical Therapy is a leading provider of physical rehabilitation services. We are a multidisciplinary practice focused on high quality patient care. Our facilities feature state of the art equipment focused on outpatient sports medicine and orthopedic conditions.
### **Responsibilities**

* Pick up and transport patients from their locations to the SportsMed PT offices and back again;
* Ensure all company vehicles are kept clean;
* Be responsible for all scheduled vehicle maintenance issues;
* Assist patients in and out of the vehicle as necessary;
* Provide great customer service to all our patients;
* Be a great team player who exemplifies the SportsMed attitude.

### **Requirements**

* A clean driving record;
* Familiarity with the Waze navigation app;
* Comfortable with common technology such as texting, email and voicemail on mobile devices;
* Self-motivated and organized;
* Ability to follow instructions and work independently;
* High School Diploma or GED;
* Minimum five years’ driving experience;

### **Benefits**

* Competitive pay
* Opportunity for advancement
* Medical, Dental, Vision and Supplemental Insurance
* 401K
* Paid Time Off
* Paid Sick Leave
* Paid Overtime
* Paid Holidays
* Pay Range: $15.13 - $16.50 per hour
